1
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:15,400
Mango.

2
00:00:16,630 --> 00:00:17,770
30 yuan.

3
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:20,600
Put it on my tab.

4
00:00:24,630 --> 00:00:25,900
Thanks, but I can't.

5
00:00:26,430 --> 00:00:27,090
Lin Liying.

6
00:00:29,770 --> 00:00:30,700
Thanks.

7
00:00:32,270 --> 00:00:34,730
I took my mom to Pink Girls' concert.

8
00:00:34,730 --> 00:00:36,100
She was so happy.

9
00:00:37,830 --> 00:00:39,170
Is it that obvious?

10
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:41,700
Just come to my place.

11
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:43,070
Look at the homework you did for me.

12
00:00:43,070 --> 00:00:44,270
Then I knew.

13
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:50,100
I have a friend.

14
00:00:50,100 --> 00:00:52,270
He's been tone-deaf since childhood.

15
00:00:52,270 --> 00:00:53,900
He really loves 'Forever in Love'...

16
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:55,100
Alright, enough.

17
00:00:59,970 --> 00:01:02,170
My writing is pretty good.

18
00:01:04,800 --> 00:01:05,770
Anyway,

19
00:01:05,770 --> 00:01:07,000
you mind my business,

20
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:07,800
I mind yours.

21
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:08,700
OK?

22
00:01:09,630 --> 00:01:10,330
But I still think

23
00:01:10,330 --> 00:01:12,270
I mind your business more often.

24
00:01:12,270 --> 00:01:13,130
Wait a second.

25
00:01:13,870 --> 00:01:15,730
There's something on your face.

26
00:01:15,730 --> 00:01:16,500
What?

27
00:01:17,570 --> 00:01:18,370
Liying.

28
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:20,170
Excuse me.

29
00:01:20,170 --> 00:01:20,870
I forgot to tell you.

30
00:01:20,870 --> 00:01:22,200
Your dad is back, right?

31
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:24,970
That's nice. Family reunion.

32
00:01:24,970 --> 00:01:26,030
Carry on.

33
00:03:30,930 --> 00:03:31,970
Hello.

34
00:03:31,970 --> 00:03:34,400
Hello. Do you have an appointment?

35
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:37,329
No. I'm looking for Mr. Deng Weiyu.

36
00:03:37,329 --> 00:03:39,329
Mr. Deng Weiyu.

37
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:42,100
You might need to wait a moment.

38
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:42,770
Hey, Amy.

39
00:03:42,770 --> 00:03:43,900
Has my package arrived?

40
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:45,300
This is Mr. Deng.

41
00:03:48,770 --> 00:03:49,900
Um, senior.

42
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:52,200
I... we've met before.

43
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,570
I'm Lin Liying.

44
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:04,370
So you want my brother to take responsibility for what happened to your family?

45
00:04:04,370 --> 00:04:06,070
Why does he bully people like this?

46
00:04:06,070 --> 00:04:08,330
Just because Linlin Breakfast Shop is rich and powerful?

47
00:04:08,330 --> 00:04:09,770
Of course not.

48
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:12,930
You're Jiang Zhihao's friend.

49
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,670
I believe you must have a sense of justice too.

50
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:19,370
Perhaps

51
00:04:19,370 --> 00:04:21,230
you can tell me what to do.

52
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:25,730
Isn't that good?

53
00:04:27,730 --> 00:04:29,530
But coming to me won't help.

54
00:04:29,530 --> 00:04:30,670
Why?

55
00:04:31,570 --> 00:04:33,600
Are you on Deng Weikang's side?

56
00:04:40,070 --> 00:04:41,470
I'll arrange for you

57
00:04:41,970 --> 00:04:44,330
to meet someone who can solve the problem.

58
00:04:57,630 --> 00:05:00,430
I just wanted to develop a regular basketball routine.

59
00:05:00,430 --> 00:05:03,170
Yet it gave someone an opportunity to take advantage.

60
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:05,700
Looks like I need to change my practice court.

61
00:05:07,930 --> 00:05:09,370
Let her in.

62
00:05:15,730 --> 00:05:17,430
The toxic toy incident.

63
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:21,570
The culprit was an inside thief from your toy factory.

64
00:05:21,570 --> 00:05:24,070
Linlin Breakfast was also a victim.

65
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:28,330
I heard you want me to take responsibility.

66
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:31,270
Because Deng Weikang is behind it all.

67
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:34,600
Don't make accusations without evidence.

68
00:05:49,570 --> 00:05:51,870
I deeply sympathize with your family's situation.

69
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:53,300
After all, I also started from nothing.

70
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:55,300
Working hard to get where I am today.

71
00:05:55,970 --> 00:05:57,100
How about this.

72
00:05:58,200 --> 00:06:00,170
In my personal capacity,

73
00:06:00,170 --> 00:06:02,970
I'll sponsor your family with funds to start over.

74
00:06:03,370 --> 00:06:04,500
How much?

75
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,370
Just tell my assistant.

76
00:06:22,130 --> 00:06:23,770
Isn't that enough?

77
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,100
An apology.

78
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:28,430
What I want is an apology.

79
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:40,600
Money is fine.

80
00:06:42,130 --> 00:06:43,700
An apology is impossible.

81
00:06:44,970 --> 00:06:46,730
Is it so hard to apologize?

82
00:06:46,730 --> 00:06:50,060
Shouldn't you apologize when you've done something wrong?

83
00:06:52,330 --> 00:06:54,670
There's no right or wrong in this matter.

84
00:06:54,670 --> 00:06:56,200
But if I apologize,

85
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:58,100
it means I'm wrong.

86
00:07:01,030 --> 00:07:01,830
I'm done playing.

87
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:03,270
Zijing, pack up.

88
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:20,330
After working with Deng Weikang for so many years

89
00:07:20,330 --> 00:07:23,100
we've actually grown more distant over time.

90
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:25,830
He doesn't care how much our costs have increased.

91
00:07:25,830 --> 00:07:27,200
Thanks to you this time,

92
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,530
we can take advantage of his troubles

93
00:07:28,530 --> 00:07:29,670
to adjust our contract.

94
00:07:29,670 --> 00:07:33,200
Contracts should evolve with the times anyway.

95
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,570
Being able to maintain a healthy partnership

96
00:07:34,570 --> 00:07:36,500
with your company Lequan

97
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:39,100
is the right path, isn't it?

98
00:07:41,470 --> 00:07:43,570
As business people,

99
00:07:44,430 --> 00:07:46,470
we need to have a long-term vision.

100
00:07:47,230 --> 00:07:48,470
Here's to you.

101
00:07:50,070 --> 00:07:51,200
To a successful partnership.

102
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,860
To a successful partnership.

103
00:07:53,770 --> 00:07:55,700
Deputy Director, your car is here.

104
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:56,300
You know I just threw up in the bathroom,

105
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:58,400
but I cleaned up thoroughly.

106
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:04,230
How is it your alcohol tolerance hasn't improved at all?

107
00:09:04,230 --> 00:09:06,900
With such poor tolerance, you still dare to ask me for another round.

108
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:08,500
Because you asked me to come.

109
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,700
Actually,

110
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:19,500
you've known about

111
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:22,500
my relationship with Weikang all along, haven't you?

112
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,570
So,

113
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:40,800
every time I chatted with you,

114
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:43,530
you knew I was trying to get information from you.

115
00:09:55,330 --> 00:09:58,130
I must have seemed ridiculous to you.

116
00:10:01,170 --> 00:10:03,700
You were blinded by love.

117
00:10:04,170 --> 00:10:06,230
You're too emotional.

118
00:10:08,130 --> 00:10:09,570
Unlike me.

119
00:10:09,970 --> 00:10:11,670
I prioritize benefits.

120
00:10:17,230 --> 00:10:18,270
Benefits.

121
00:10:18,270 --> 00:10:19,570
Money.

122
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:23,700
Just throw money at me.

123
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:25,930
Buy this business

124
00:10:26,470 --> 00:10:28,700
and we can turn the page on all this.

125
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,730
Do you really need more money?

126
00:10:34,670 --> 00:10:36,630
I do. The more the better.

127
00:10:37,630 --> 00:10:38,500
That's alcohol.

128
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:40,570
Stop drinking.

129
00:10:41,300 --> 00:10:42,570
Drink water.

130
00:10:48,970 --> 00:10:52,300
You don't know that everyone calls me 'Clear-headed Deng.'

131
00:10:56,270 --> 00:10:58,700
I know exactly which friends

132
00:10:59,470 --> 00:11:01,570
I should and shouldn't make,

133
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:03,900
I'm very clear about that.

134
00:11:29,900 --> 00:11:31,570
Let me tell you,

135
00:11:33,730 --> 00:11:36,300
I resigned today.

136
00:11:38,270 --> 00:11:40,800
I'm going back to work at my mother's company.

137
00:11:48,970 --> 00:11:50,430
In the future,

138
00:11:50,430 --> 00:11:52,830
we should still go out drinking like this.

139
00:11:52,830 --> 00:11:54,470
I need a drinking buddy.

140
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:57,500
Of course.

141
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:05,870
Where's my glass?

142
00:12:06,270 --> 00:12:07,800
No, are you sure?

143
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:09,630
I'm sure. Are you sure?

144
00:12:09,630 --> 00:12:11,370
Fill it up for me.

145
00:12:12,370 --> 00:12:13,800
You asked for it.

146
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:15,200
Here.

147
00:12:26,330 --> 00:12:27,470
Keep drinking.

148
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:29,000
Drink it all.

149
00:12:31,970 --> 00:12:34,000
Besides successfully retaining Lequan.

150
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:34,970
The Farm Chicken Burger

151
00:12:34,970 --> 00:12:37,600
has also cleared the stigma of hunger marketing,

152
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:40,300
and even boosted the entire March performance,

153
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:43,430
making last month's revenue reach a historic high.

154
00:12:43,430 --> 00:12:45,200
Thank you all for working hard with me,

155
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,600
turning crisis into opportunity.

156
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,870
Yes!

157
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:50,770
Amazing results!

158
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,630
Very good.

159
00:12:53,930 --> 00:12:55,100
Weijie.

160
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:55,770
Yes,

161
00:12:55,770 --> 00:12:57,230
all the progress and reports

162
00:12:57,230 --> 00:12:58,960
need to be properly organized.

163
00:12:59,670 --> 00:13:00,600
When the Deputy General Manager returns,

164
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,460
we'll give him a thorough report.

165
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:07,630
Alright,

166
00:13:07,630 --> 00:13:08,970
thank you all for your hard work.

167
00:13:08,970 --> 00:13:09,830
Tonight,

168
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:11,800
everyone pick a nice restaurant,

169
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:13,130
the company's treat.

170
00:13:13,130 --> 00:13:14,830
Thank you, Chairman.

171
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:16,930
It's on the Deputy GM.

172
00:13:17,470 --> 00:13:20,170
Thank you, Deputy GM. Thanks to our absent Deputy GM.

173
00:13:20,170 --> 00:13:21,530
Thank you, Deputy GM.

174
00:13:39,230 --> 00:13:40,530
Dad, Weiyu.

175
00:13:40,530 --> 00:13:41,700
Sit down.

176
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:50,200
Since returning from Japan,

177
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:52,200
you've been at the company for quite a while.

178
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:54,600
Do you have any thoughts about your future?

179
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:56,930
I might continue working with the Deputy GM and Director

180
00:13:56,930 --> 00:13:59,000
to gain more experience

181
00:13:59,430 --> 00:14:01,500
and see how I can help in the future.

182
00:14:05,230 --> 00:14:06,890
Is that really what you think?

183
00:14:14,730 --> 00:14:16,970
Haven't you ever thought

184
00:14:17,230 --> 00:14:18,600
that one day

185
00:14:19,070 --> 00:14:20,400
you, Deng Weiyu,

186
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:22,570
might lead the entire Linlin Group?

187
00:14:37,730 --> 00:14:38,570
People with ambition

188
00:14:38,570 --> 00:14:40,800
are the ones who build successful careers.

189
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:41,900
Those who seek comfort

190
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:43,960
will never rise above their station.

191
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:49,900
If I give you an opportunity to prove yourself

192
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:52,400
by managing...

193
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:53,930
the Linlin flagship store,

194
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:58,730
do you think you're up to the task?

195
00:15:08,170 --> 00:15:10,170
What should I do? Should I answer it?

196
00:15:10,630 --> 00:15:11,500
If you don't answer,

197
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:13,630
he'll think you're incompetent.

198
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,530
Fine, I'll answer it.

199
00:15:16,530 --> 00:15:17,400
If you answer,

200
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:19,430
you'll be just another Deng Weijie.

201
00:15:21,630 --> 00:15:23,430
So what should I do?

202
00:15:24,130 --> 00:15:25,630
He wants you to show ambition.

203
00:15:25,630 --> 00:15:28,100
So show him your ambition.

204
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:30,000
But don't follow his script.

205
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,730
Because he already knows the plot.

206
00:15:31,730 --> 00:15:33,330
No matter how well you act,

207
00:15:33,330 --> 00:15:35,900
to him it's just icing on the cake.

208
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,000
You need to play a character

209
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,370
that he can't figure out,

210
00:15:39,370 --> 00:15:41,130
yet can't help but admire.

211
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:45,070
Keep talking.

212
00:15:45,070 --> 00:15:46,470
That's not playing fair.

213
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:48,730
Answer it.

214
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:51,270
But it's not the flagship store.

215
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,170
Excuse me,

216
00:16:12,170 --> 00:16:14,200
don't you open at six?

217
00:16:16,870 --> 00:16:18,530
No matter what you order, you have to wait.

218
00:16:18,530 --> 00:16:20,030
Write it yourself.

219
00:16:22,470 --> 00:16:25,330
Don't you have digital ordering now?

220
00:16:25,330 --> 00:16:26,800
I don't know how to use it.

221
00:16:32,330 --> 00:16:33,430
Thank you.

222
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:41,730
Um...

223
00:16:41,730 --> 00:16:42,970
I'm sorry,

224
00:16:42,970 --> 00:16:45,030
I ordered black tea.

225
00:16:45,030 --> 00:16:46,500
The black tea is over there.

226
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:47,670
It'll take an hour to brew a new pot.

227
00:16:47,670 --> 00:16:48,800
Do you want to wait?

228
00:16:49,970 --> 00:16:51,800
Yes or no?

229
00:16:52,370 --> 00:16:54,200
I'll pass for now. Thanks.

230
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:00,230
Morning.

231
00:17:00,230 --> 00:17:01,600
Morning.

232
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,100
You're late again.

233
00:17:04,069 --> 00:17:06,329
Heroes always arrive fashionably late.

234
00:17:07,270 --> 00:17:08,829
Besides, I'm not the last one.

235
00:17:08,829 --> 00:17:10,270
Fatty isn't here yet.

236
00:17:13,730 --> 00:17:14,500
What's this?

237
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:15,930
Mind your own business.

238
00:17:23,970 --> 00:17:26,329
Is he drinking soy milk?

239
00:17:26,329 --> 00:17:29,130
It's not expired, so I can drink it. What's the problem?

240
00:17:29,130 --> 00:17:30,700
If it's not expired, we should recycle it.

241
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:32,400
Otherwise what are we going to drink?

242
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,730
Couldn't you have said that earlier?

243
00:17:33,730 --> 00:17:34,900
All muscles, no brains.

244
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:36,830
You chicken-brain.

245
00:17:36,830 --> 00:17:38,570
Go wipe it clean.

246
00:17:42,470 --> 00:17:43,500
Make sure it's clean.

247
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:45,100
Or Ah Fei will scold us later.

248
00:17:52,570 --> 00:17:53,670
I'd like a

249
00:17:53,670 --> 00:17:55,000
peanut ham and egg sandwich.

250
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,230
Okay, coming right up.

251
00:17:56,230 --> 00:17:57,300
With a black tea.

252
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:58,500
Okay.

253
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:02,030
What's 'dragon and phoenix'?

254
00:18:02,030 --> 00:18:03,470
Ham and egg.

255
00:18:03,470 --> 00:18:04,500
It's a combo.

256
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:07,230
How many times do I have to tell you? Why are you so stupid?

257
00:18:07,230 --> 00:18:08,800
Jiang Zhihao, let me tell you.

258
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:09,570
If this happens again tomorrow,

259
00:18:09,570 --> 00:18:10,970
I'm done with this job.

260
00:18:10,970 --> 00:18:11,930
Don't worry,

261
00:18:11,930 --> 00:18:13,430
there won't be a tomorrow.

262
00:18:13,430 --> 00:18:14,700
What do you mean?

263
00:18:17,870 --> 00:18:19,530
Hello, dear friends.

264
00:18:19,530 --> 00:18:21,670
I'll be taking a few months off.

265
00:18:21,670 --> 00:18:22,970
Thank you all for your support.

266
00:18:22,970 --> 00:18:25,000
Today I've prepared 10 different dishes

267
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,270
for you to choose from.

268
00:18:26,270 --> 00:18:28,130
No discount for bulk purchases.

269
00:18:29,170 --> 00:18:30,100
Ma'am, yours is ready.

270
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:31,170
Two of them.

271
00:18:31,970 --> 00:18:33,200
Thank you.

272
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:35,030
It's a thank-you sale.

273
00:18:35,030 --> 00:18:36,230
50 each.

274
00:18:36,230 --> 00:18:37,100
Take your pick.

275
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:38,170
Okay.

276
00:18:38,170 --> 00:18:39,200
Jiang Zhihao,

277
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:40,600
what do you mean?

278
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:41,830
You're quitting?

279
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:42,900
Without discussing it with me first?

280
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:44,270
Thank-you sale!

281
00:18:44,270 --> 00:18:45,270
50 dollars each.

282
00:18:45,270 --> 00:18:45,970
Take a look.

283
00:18:45,970 --> 00:18:47,570
Lots of options today.

284
00:18:59,330 --> 00:19:00,930
Aren't you going to explain?

285
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:03,930
Did you see Mrs. Chen's expression?

286
00:19:03,930 --> 00:19:05,270
She was so sad.

287
00:19:05,270 --> 00:19:06,530
I'm telling you, I'm going to sell frozen food packages.

